      • set

        @RobotCommand(commandName="set",
              paramNames={"Forward Speed","Button Wait Time","Reverse Speed","Return Wait Time"})
public void set(@Bounds(min=0,max=255)
                                         java.lang.Integer forwardSpeed,
                                         @Bounds(min=0,max=2147483647)
                                         java.lang.Integer buttonWaitTime,
                                         @Bounds(min=0,max=255)
                                         java.lang.Integer reverseSpeed,
                                         @Bounds(min=0,max=2147483647)
                                         java.lang.Integer returnWaitTime)
         throws java.io.IOException,
                java.lang.InterruptedException
        The set command. This command sets the parameters for the stroke move. It does not return until complete, but can be interrupted.
        Parameters:
        forwardSpeed - the motor's speed when driving the finger away from the starting position. Between 0 and 255, inclusive.
        buttonWaitTime - the amount of time, in ms, the robot should wait once the finger hits the limit switch.
        reverseSpeed - the motor's speed when driving the finger back to the starting position. Between 0 and 255, inclusive.
        returnWaitTime - the amount of time to wait once the finger has returned to its original position.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if there is a problem communicating with the robot.
        java.lang.InterruptedException - if the move is interrupted.

                                           @Bounds(min=0,max=255)
                                           java.lang.Integer speed)
           throws java.io.IOException,
                  java.lang.InterruptedException
        The reset command. This command causes the robot to drive the finger towards the starting position.
        Parameters:
        time - the amount of time the finger will be in motion, in ms.
        speed - the motor's speed, between 0 and 255 inclusive.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if there is a problem communicating with the robot.
        java.lang.InterruptedException - if the move is interrupted.
